column5: from Environment Canada  Storm totals may be 20 to 30 centimetres along and east of a line from Long Point to the Golden Horseshoe then to Petawawa. There is potential for 30 to 50 centimetres of snow over the Niagara Peninsula and parts of eastern Ontario.
Umm... good luck with that... all the storms have missed the north this year....
WAY TO GO!!!!!!! u just had to jinx it didn't u,
